               <msContents>
                  <summary>Hai ben Sherira's Book of Bargaining and Selling</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <title xml:lang="he">מקח וממכר</title>
                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Meḳaḥ u-mimkar</title>
                  <author key="person_63993515">
                     <persName>Hai ben Sherira, 939-1038</persName>
                     <persName xml:lang="he">האי בן שרירא, גאון, 939-1038</persName>
                  </author>
                  <editor role="scr">
                     <persName>Gershom ben Solomon</persName>
                     <persName>גרשם בן שלמה</persName>
                  </editor>                  
                     <note>The colophon (<locus>fol. 102v</locus>, even under ultra-violet lamp or with infra-red photography, is partly illegible and has been partly rewritten. It is surrounded by micrography, which seems to contain the beg. of the colophon.</note>
                     <note>The colophon is followed by a partly illegible poem. Many letters in the poem are pointed out, and a late Ashkenazic cursive hand combined them into a long genealogy:<lang xml:lang="he">חזקיה ברבי אליקים בר יוסף ברבי אורי בר אליעזר בנו</lang> (<lang xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Ḥezeḳiah varbi 'Eliḳim bar Yosef barbi 'Ori bar 'Eliezar beno</lang>), but the pointing out is most likely not by the original scribe.</note>
                    <textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>  
                  </msItem>                  
               </msContents>
